Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.64,0:00:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.63,0:00:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.88,0:00:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.12,0:00:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.13,0:00:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.81,0:00:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.11,0:01:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.19,0:01:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.97,0:01:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So you came, Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.64,0:01:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was a little concerned that the shock of losing Jounouchi would break you...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.64,0:01:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...but it seems I worried over nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.44,0:01:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is our fated Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.65,0:01:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My Obelisk? Or your Osiris?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The time to settle this has finally come!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.48,0:01:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I'll defeat you, Yugi, and gather all three God Cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I'll show you all that I will obtain the title of Duel King!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Three Knights Used to Call God"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.09,0:02:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using the effects of Exchange, I add Osiris to my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.89,0:02:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll return it to you for {\b0}now{\b1}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.48,0:02:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I'm the one who's going to gather all the God Cards in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.52,0:02:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And even if you're holding the god in your hands, you can't do a thing to play him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My Obelisk is sealed on the field for another two turns...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.41,0:02:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...once I complete the XY-Dragon Cannon's Ultimate Fusion, it'll blow away all of your Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't let you sacrifice three Monsters to Summon God to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Two turns for me, on the other hand, is more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The moment the Lightforce Sword wears off, God will descend!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.35,0:02:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's true I got the Osiris card back into my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Exchange was a dangerous gamble...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:03:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Exchange allowed each of us to take a card from the other player...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You choose one as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.04,0:03:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Life Shaver...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.21,0:03:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It forces the opponent to discard cards from their hand equal to the amount of turns it was face-down on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Hand Elimination Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Osiris the Heaven Dragon's Attack Points are determined by the number of cards in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.22,0:03:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If he uses the Life Shaver\N to reduce my hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}it will be rendered useless, regardless of whether it's a god or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no doubt about it... Kaiba will play Life Shaver face-down this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.19,0:03:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Yugi! It's your turn now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Big Shield Gardna\N in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then set a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:04:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I can do for now is try to defend myself against XY-Dragon Cannon's attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.92,0:04:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph... Looks like\N defending is all you can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can crush you even {\i1}with{\i0} my god sealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Two more turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.52,0:04:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba will most certainly\N Summon Obelisk the second\N Ligthforce Sword disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once that happens, Yugi will have\N no hope of Summoning Osiris.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nor will he have any chance of {\b0}winning{\b1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.70,0:04:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't {\b0}disappoint{\b1} me now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You must continue to grow\N before I sacrifice you\N to the depths of darkness...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's no fun crushing someone\N who's already half-dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.08,0:04:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You must writhe in\N more pain before that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.55,0:04:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I'm going to make you suffer\N the {\b0}ultimate{\b1} pain, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to get the creeps...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.89,0:04:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.89,0:04:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Forget about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:04:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Honda sure is running late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The engine in the Battle Ship\N took quite a hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.03,0:05:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe even the radio is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.11,0:05:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean a\N rescue helicopter won't come?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... big brother will...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax, Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.92,0:05:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0} will find a way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.00,0:05:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right. For now, we just have\N to wait and believe in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.98,0:05:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sweet! It's my turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I did it! I'm the best drawer around!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon Axe Raider in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Attack Petit Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Eh!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hell yeah! Now your Life Points hit zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.67,0:06:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dammit! This sucks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I did it! I made it to the second round, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Uh... Honda!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An... zu?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where'd Gramps go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What the heck... Don't tell me they\N didn't stay and watch my match...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those guys are heartless...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.65,0:06:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where'd you all go...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.70,0:06:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Battle Ship speaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Someone answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.62,0:06:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.08,0:06:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be faster to just\N fix the Battle Ship's engine?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got someone working on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'll take a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's got to be {\i1}something{\i0} we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.02,0:07:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rishid... The gods are about to arise once again...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.82,0:07:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destiny has continued moving\N for the past 3,000 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.78,0:07:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And their fight has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.03,0:07:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fate itself has forced them to clash.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destiny began to\N make its move on that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.25,0:07:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.13,0:07:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.92,0:07:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the image carved above him is the Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the one standing\N beside their king, the Pharaoh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He is known as the "White Beast Handler".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.06,0:07:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the creature carved above him is without a doubt...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.14,0:07:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.86,0:07:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The young Pharaoh controls the Magician of Black Magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And one of his own priests, The White Beast Handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.95,0:07:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This palette depicts a Duelist battleground that took place several millenniums ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is what I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.29,0:08:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perhaps fate itself leads the souls
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}of the king and priest depicted here to battle in present day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even now, after 3,000 years pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is nothing but crazy talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I overestimated you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.22,0:08:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look closely at the top of the mural.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The three depicted atop the palette, from left to right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Great War God Obelisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.27,0:08:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Osiris the Heaven Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Winged Sun Dragon of Ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Three Illusionary Beasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In our present day and age, they have come to be known as "God Cards".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}God Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.37,0:08:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pegasus created the three rare cards after viewing this palette.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You probably have heard rumors of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is said that whoever acquires these three rare cards
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.67,0:08:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}will become a legend among the world of Duels, and be granted the highest ranking Duelist's title...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The title "King of Kings".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.47,0:09:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This card.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.23,0:09:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Great War God Obelisk!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.94,0:09:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the only card out of the three that was not stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.61,0:09:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order to retrieve the other two, I am entrusting you with the Great War God Obelisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.86,0:09:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're {\b0}entrusting{\b1} me with this card?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you sure you can trust me that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.74,0:09:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What will you do if I retrieve the rare cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and refuse to give them back?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.25,0:09:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The battle between\N those chosen by the God Cards has\N been going on for 3,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.22,0:09:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And no one knows\N how this battle will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Which one of them will achieve victory\N and their goals along with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Which one of them\N will invoke God first?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.99,0:10:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And what will occur after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All we can do is silently watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No matter {\b0}what{\b1} happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba...! Kaiba...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Before he can even\N think of invoking Osiris,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my Monster will\N crush all of his sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However I do it, I won't let him Summon his god!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I'll be the one\N to Summon my god first!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.91,0:10:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Like strings to a puppet,\N everything is moving exactly\N the way I want them to!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.38,0:10:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.67,0:10:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A reverse...! That card is\N most likely Life Shaver...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You no longer\N have no chance of winning!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you are prepared to lose, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.85,0:11:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Z-Metal Caterpillar\N in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.85,0:11:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The third Magnet Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.36,0:11:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment the Magnet Monsters\N X, Y and Z are present on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.03,0:11:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their Special Ability is activated!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.92,0:11:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuse together, XYZ-Dragon Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}2800 Attack Points...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}None of the Monsters on my field have enough points to defend against that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.81,0:11:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Plus, the seal on Obelisk\N will be lifted next turn...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And he can use his XYZ\N to Summon the god!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.44,0:11:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not too shabby, Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.19,0:12:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd expect nothing less of the man who defeated my elder sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.66,0:12:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XYZ-Dragon Cannon attacks!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.08,0:12:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll destroy Big Shield Gardna\N with this attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.75,0:12:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XYZ Hyper Cannon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've destroyed all\N your Monsters on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.97,0:12:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'll smash your {\i1}soul{\i0}\N without a trace!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba, I knew from that start\N that you'd destroy my\N lower Defense Big Shield Gardna.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.19,0:12:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've given me a chance to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.69,0:12:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.28,0:12:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Soul Rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.86,0:12:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.20,0:12:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment my Monster is defeated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.37,0:12:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this card lets me\N pay 1000 of my Life Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.62,0:12:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and call one Four-Star Monster\N out onto the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the card I pick...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.50,0:13:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon King's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.92,0:13:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the King and Queen\N are both on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.84,0:13:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"King" and "Queen"...\N Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.05,0:13:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.97,0:13:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Special Summon\N the "Jack" card!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A three-Monster combo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.81,0:13:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like your Magnet Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my deck, too, contains Monsters\N to help me Summon God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.90,0:13:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! Jack's Knight!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.41,0:13:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I have three\N sacrifices on my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.08,0:13:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in this situation where I\N was completely on top of this game...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.21,0:13:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi somehow managed\N to Summon God first?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.01,0:13:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.01,0:13:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I offer three tributes to the Heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Summon Osiris the Heaven Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.31,0:14:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris the Heaven Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.73,0:14:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the gods has\N finally been Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.65,0:14:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now {\i1}that{\i0} was quite a {\i1}surprise{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think Yugi would be able to\N Summon God first in a situation like {\i1}this{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.57,0:14:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fascinating!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba! It looks like the tables just\N turned when I invoked Osiris.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, we'll see about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.71,0:14:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.67,0:15:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris the Heaven Dragon's Attack Points are determined by the number of cards in the player's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this turn, your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...only holds three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.76,0:15:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris the Heaven Dragon \Nhas only 3000 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But {\i1}your{\i0} XYZ-Dragon Cannon has only {\i1}2800 Attack Points{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can easily destroy it\N on my attack this turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.86,0:15:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if I do, you'll lose your sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.61,0:15:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus you wouldn't be able to\N Summon Obelisk next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.99,0:15:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then go ahead and {\i1}try{\i0} attacking...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.49,0:15:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So confident, even in his position...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba knows what will happen\N if I destroy his XYZ-Dragon Cannon\N with God's attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is he hiding something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.63,0:15:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's only a 200 point difference\N between Osiris and his Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought his reverse card\N must be the Life Shaver\N that he drew from my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.47,0:15:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But if he plays it after only\N just activating it this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't have to\N discard a card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.90,0:16:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! what's the matter, Yugi?!\N Go ahead and attack me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.73,0:16:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Heh! Is Kaiba merely {\b0}bluffing{\b1}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stopping God's attack so easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Stopping Yugi from\N making a move because of\N one mere reverse card...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're not bad at all, Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.33,0:16:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether you attack or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you won't be able to stop me\N from achieving victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Suppose that reverse card\N is a card that can raise\N XYZ-Dragon Cannon's Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.84,0:16:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Osiris could die!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.22,0:16:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I don't attack on this turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...he'll Summon Obelisk on his next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And there's a good chance\N he's just bluffing and that reverse card\N is what I thought it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.73,0:16:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's a good chance\N that it's just Life Shaver...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.03,0:16:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In that case, I can't\N back down at this point!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:17:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris the Heaven Dragon! Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.71,0:17:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew you would!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.12,0:17:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thunder Force!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.92,0:17:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.63,0:17:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interdimensional Matter Transporter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it... wasn't Life Shaver!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.39,0:17:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I transfer XYZ-Dragon Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to this Magic Effect,\N Osiris loses its attack target!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.28,0:17:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its attack is wasted!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.57,0:17:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.03,0:17:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure, but something just came out of the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... the power of Osiris...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something must be happening\N at the Duel Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.01,0:17:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is Kaiba Corporation speaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.30,0:18:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please respond, Battle Ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is Kaiba Corporation speaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.89,0:18:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please respond!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.27,0:18:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The connection...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're connected!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.90,0:18:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're sending a helicopter\N as we speak!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.78,0:18:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's gonna be fine now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.16,0:18:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I'll go tell Shizuka-{\i1}chan{\i0}\N and the guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.28,0:18:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the radioactive interference is gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can send video too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I'm off to cheer\N for my big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.88,0:18:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XYZ-Dragon Cannon... vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.56,0:18:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like your turn\N was just wasted, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:19:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A reverse to protect\N your tributes for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... My turn isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.16,0:19:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll place a reverse card as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.92,0:19:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's voluntarily playing\N a card from his hand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's absurd...! He only has\N two cards left in his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Does he not realize that\N next turn I'll Summon Obelisk\N with 4000 Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Kaiba! It's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,XYZ-Dragon Cannon might even be\N strong enough to destroy Osiris\N {\i1}without{\i0} Summoning a god!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This turn it's {\i1}my{\i0} turn\N to test {\i1}your{\i0} will, Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prattle on as you like,\N but my next move is already decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.62,0:19:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's now {\i1}my{\i0} turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.96,0:19:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Obelisk will return to my hand,\N now that Lightforce Sword's effect\N has finally disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.72,0:20:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will show you God...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I offer XYZ-Dragon Cannon\N as a sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.52,0:20:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obelisk, the God of Destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.02,0:20:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bend to my unshakable will!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And descend to my domain!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.53,0:20:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shake Heaven and Earth\N with your unsurpassed power!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And bring me {\i1}victory{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.08,0:20:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Summon The Great War God Obelisk!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here it comes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.34,0:20:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Such massive power...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the Great War God, Obelisk!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:20:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've finally\N shown yourself, Obelisk!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The battle of gods has {\i1}finally begun{\i0}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Great War God Obelisk...\N What immense power swells inside it...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.95,0:21:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My entire body is shivering\N with anticipation and fear\N like I've never felt!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.71,0:21:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The clash of these titans,\N the {\i1}gods{\i0}, has finally come!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.04,0:21:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will defeat your Osiris...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.59,0:21:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and gather all the\N gods into my hands!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with the title of "Duel King"!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.15,0:21:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two gods have finally been Summoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Osiris the Heaven Dragon and The Great War God Obelisk!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Against such excessive power,the sky splits and the Earth trembles!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.70,0:21:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both Yugi and Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} deploy all of their strongest tactics in this fierce showdown between gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.41,0:21:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again and again, they are met with a tie!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.66,0:22:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And just as the two gods are about to clash one final time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.13,0:22:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something begins to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.17,0:22:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.25,0:22:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Clash! Osiris VS Obelisk"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.84,0:22:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.20,0:22:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.10,0:22:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.44,0:22:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.05,0:22:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.44,0:22:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.00,0:22:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.62,0:22:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.38,0:22:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.47,0:23:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.39,0:23:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.12,0:23:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.08,0:23:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
